49-6-3507. Administration of assessments for recipients.
(a) As a condition of receiving a scholarship pursuant to this part, recipients in
any of the grades three through eleven (3-11) must be annually administered the same
Tennessee comprehensive assessment program (TCAP) tests required for students
enrolled in a public school in this state in any of the grades three through eleven (3-11).
(b) Each private school that enrolls recipients shall annually administer the
TCAP tests required in subsection (a) to the recipients enrolled in the school, and shall
provide each recipient's results on the TCAP tests to the recipient's parent.
(c) If, in any school year, recipients enrolled in a private school perform, on
average, fifteen percent (15%) lower on the TCAP tests administered pursuant to this
section, as compared to the average statewide performance of students enrolled in
public schools on the same TCAP tests administered in the same year, then,
notwithstanding ยง 49-6-3502(4), the private school is ineligible to enroll recipients in any
subsequent school year for purposes of the program.
(d) By June 30, 2026, and by each June 30 thereafter, each private school shall
provide the results of the TCAP tests administered to recipients pursuant to subsection
(a) to the office of research and education accountability in the office of the comptroller
of the treasury. A private school may provide TCAP test results using aggregated,
deidentified data; provided, that the data must be provided on a form developed by the
office of research and education accountability and in a manner that allows the office of
